article.headline: Trump raised $210 million in August, below Biden's haul of $364.5 million
article.body: President Donald Trump's re-election campaign and its affiliates on Wednesday announced they raised more than $210 million in August. The haul is well below Democratic challenger Joe Biden's August fundraising total of $364.5 million, and it comes after Trump said on Tuesday that he might spend his own money on his re-election campaign.
